== DNA ==
DNA is a Python program that analyzes a DNA sequence and compares it against a CSV database of individuals to determine a match based on Short Tandem Repeats (STRs). It identifies the longest run of each STR in the sequence and compares the counts to each profile in the database. 

== Sentimental Credit ==
Sentimental Credit is a Python version of the Credit C program that validates credit card numbers using Luhnâ€™s Algorithm. It identifies the card type (e.g., AMEX, MasterCard, VISA) by analyzing number length and starting digits. 

== Sentimental Hello ==
Sentimental Hello is a simple Python program that outputs a personalized greeting based on user input. It serves as an introductory exercise in user interaction and basic syntax.

== Sentimental Mario ==
Sentimental Mario is a Python recreation of the Mario pyramid problem, generating half-pyramids of hashes (#) based on user-specified height. It practices nested loops, input validation, and control flow. 

== Sentimental Readability ==
Sentimental Readability is a Python program that computes the Coleman-Liau index to estimate the U.S. grade level required to understand a given text. It calculates the number of letters, words, and sentences to determine and output a readability grade.
